<TEXT>
<P>
 Day for Night (Bravo Thursday at 7 p.m.; Friday at midnight) is Francois 
Truffaut's delightful, compassionate 1973 insider's look at those involved in 
trying to make a foolish movie. 
</P>
<P>
 Dr. Ehrlich's Magic Bullet (Showtime Friday at 8 a.m.) is a tremendously 
intelligent and engaging 1940 film biography of the 19th-Century scientist -- 
superbly played by Edward G. Robinson -- who developed a cure for syphilis. 
</P>
<P>
 Hotel Terminus: The Life and Times of Klaus Barbie (KCET Saturday at 9 p.m.): 
To watch Marcel Ophuls' Oscar-winning 1988 documentary on the late, sadistic 
Gestapo chief Klaus Barbie, "The Butcher of Lyon," is like experiencing a great 
novel and a real-life detective story. 
