<TEXT>
<P>
 FLOWERING INFERNO: Tales of Sinking Hearts by Rima de Vallbona, translated 
from the Spanish by Lillian Lorca de Tagle (Latin American Literary Review 
Press: $ ?? ; 92 pp., paperback original). These extremely brief short stories 
depict a world of magical realism in which reality grows tenuous. A student 
discovers Circe lurking in a modern university; a 90-year-old grandmother gives 
up tyrannizing to become a bowling champion. Intriguing, if uneven, work from a 
noted Costa Rican writer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
