<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' PICKS: 'ONE FALSE MOVE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Almost sent directly to TV, this bleakly amusing and truly moving film by 
director Carl Franklin proved to be the sleeper of 1992.Dramatic and 
suspenseful, it charts a collision course involving three losers on the run. 
They include Billy Bob Thornton, who also wrote the script with Bob Epperson, 
Cynda Williams and Michael Beach. Jim Metzler and Earl Billings play two Los 
Angeles cops in pursuit and Bill Paxton (pictured) portrays a naive Arkansas 
sheriff. Be warned: The film opens with a blood bath that communicates the 
reality of violence without exploiting it (TMC Tuesday at 8 p.m.). Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</TEXT>
