<TEXT>
<P>
 ** Richard Marx, "Paid Vacation," Capitol. Remember Player? The 
Sanford/Townsend Band? Well, Richard Marx does, along with, in his better 
moments, the late-era Raspberries.His fourth album, made with his usual stable 
of collaborators, is a combination of the sort of pasty rock made by these '70s 
forebears and some schlocky ballads that are produced prettily enough to be 
memorable. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). JEAN ROSENBLUTH 
