<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHERINE TURMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * 1/2 David Lee Roth, "Your Filthy Little Mouth," Reprise. The king -- make 
that former king -- of testosterone-fueled party rock -- is back with the 
fourth installment in his post-Van Halen career.Unfortunately, what made 
Diamond Dave shine on earlier efforts -- maniac energy, campy humor and catchy 
choruses -- is absent. In its place we have Rasta Dave doing the 
reggae-flavored "No Big Thing" and Country Dave in a duet with Travis Tritt, 
low-lights in a 14-song exercise in banality. 
</P>
<P>
