<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: John Lydon (formerly Johnny Rotten) has written an 
autobiography and, as might be expected, the title alone should raise plenty of 
eyebrows: "Rotten: No Irish, No Blacks, No Dogs." Those groups, though, 
shouldn't take too much offense -- excerpts of the book, which is due in stores 
Friday, confirm the well-known fact that Lydon isn't really fond of too many 
people.  
</P>
<P>
 Among the targets are the late Sex Pistol Sid Vicious ("He was so embarrassing 
that I kept as far away from him as I could") and the band's manager, Malcolm 
McLaren ("poxy scum"). 
</P>
</TEXT>
