<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TBS Cats and Dogs Cartoon Marathon (Sunday at 3 p.m.) features the best cat 
and dog cartoons from the TBS library: Tom & Jerry, Droopy, Sylvester, Pepe Le 
Pew and Spike and his son Tike. Also Elmer Fudd, Bugs Bunny and Porky Pig 
tangle with cats and dogs. 
</P>
<P>
 David L. Lander (Squiggy) guests on The Bob Newhart Show (Sunday at 10:30 p.m 
on Nickelodeon) in an episode in which Bob's first book turns out to be a dud. 
</P>
<P>
 Former football great Bubba White guests on McCloud (Monday at 6 a.m. on A&E). 
</P>
<P>
 Louis Jourdan plays a diabolical food critic who poisons a restaurant owner on 
Columbo (Monday at 12:30 p.m. on A&E). 
</P>
<P>
 Morey Amsterdam guests on The Partridge Family (Monday at 8 p.m. on 
Nickelodeon) in an episode in which Danny tries to be a comedian. 
</P>
<P>
 Artie Johnson is a guest on The Dick Van Dyke Show (Tuesday at 11 p.m. on 
Nickelodeon) in the episode in which Rob can't make up his mind whether he 
should become a city council candidate. 
</P>
<P>
 A very young Kurt Russell plays a jungle boy on Gilligan's Island (Wednesday 
at 5:05 a.m. on TBS). 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, TBS presents two special Matlock mysteries: "The Investigation" 
( at 9:05 p.m.), with Shaun Cassidy, and "The Ambassador" (at 11:05 p.m.), with 
David Ogden Stiers. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary believes a handsome priest (Ed Flanders) is leaving the church because he 
has a crush on her on The Mary Tyler Moore Show (Wednesday at 10:30 p.m. on 
Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Stella Stevens guests on Police Story (Thursday at 2 p.m. on A&E) as a tough 
policewoman who thwarts a cocaine-smuggling network but loses her husband in 
the process. 
</P>
<P>
 TNT presents the two-part "Tyger, Tyger" episode of Dr. Kildare (Thursday at 
midnight); Richard Chamberlain and Raymond Massey star. 
</P>
