<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 TRI-CITIES DIRECTORS STILL DRAW BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In the article "Past Grand Juries Gave Warning of Potential for Abuse at 
Water Districts" (March 22), a misleading statement was made with reference to 
the elimination of each director's approximate $500 monthly health benefits 
package by Tri-Cities Municipal Water District. 
</P>
<P>
 The change in district policy to eliminate these benefits will become 
effective in January, 1995, and will apply to all newly elected or reelected 
directors (voted 3-2). To date, two of the current directors (Board President 
William Mecham and Treasurer Craig Strickland) continue to take full benefits 
-- Blue Cross, Delta Dental and Vision Care -- for themselves and families over 
the protests of most of the district's constituents. 
</P>
<P>
 RAY L. BENEDICKTUS 
</P>
<P>
 Director 
</P>
<P>
 Tri-Cities Municipal Water District 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 
</P>
