<P>
NEWSWIRE: TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fourth-seeded Mary Pierce of France overpowered wild-card entry Asa Carlsson 
of Sweden, 6-2, 6-2, in the semifinals of the $400,000 Virginia Slims of 
Houston. Skiing  
</P>
<P>
 Thomas Grandi of Banff, Canada, went from sixth place after the first run to 
win the men's giant slalom in the U.S. Alpine Championships at Winter Park, 
Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 Grandi, .65 seconds behind first-run leader Chris Puckett of Crested Butte, 
Colo., had a second run of 1 minute, 10.08 seconds that was more than a second 
faster than any other skier. That gave him a combined time of 2:17.71. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremy Nobis of Park City, Utah, finished second in 2:18.46. Puckett was third 
in 2:19.18. 
