<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / NCAA WOMEN'S TOURNAMENTS; WOMEN'S ROUNDUP; TAR HEELS 
ADVANCE TO FINAL FOUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 North Carolina is going to the Final Four, and this time it's the women's 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 Tonya Sampson scored 30 points and the No. 4 Tar Heels advanced to the Final 
Four for the first time by rallying in the second half to defeat No. 3 
Connecticut, 81-69, in the East Regional final Saturday at Piscataway, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 North Carolina will play West Regional winner Purdue in the national semifinal 
next Saturday at Richmond, Va. 
</P>
<P>
 "This proves we can play with and beat the best teams," senior center Sylvia 
Crawley said. "The next two games are just going to be a matter of who wants it 
more." 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the 12th in a row for the third-seeded Tar Heels (31-2) and it 
snapped a 21-game winning streak for top-seeded Connecticut (30-3). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 16 Alabama 96, No. 2 Penn State 82 -- Betsy Harris scored 25 points at 
Austin, Tex. to lead Alabama (26-6), which will meet Louisiana Tech. Helen 
Holloway led Penn State (28-3) with 25 points. 
</P>
