<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST RIPS EXPLOSIVE RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Toby Sanchez set a school record with three home runs, but Rancho Santiago and 
ace pitcher Brian Hoalton were upset by Golden West, 12-7, Saturday in an 
Orange Empire Conference baseball game at Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez, who has seven homers this season, finished with six runs batted in.It 
was the second loss for Hoalton (5-2), who had begun his community college 
pitching career with 17 consecutive victories over two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Flanagan was two for five with three RBIs for Golden West (11-12, 5-7). 
Rancho Santiago is 20-6 and 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 12, Cypress 8 -- Chad Smith had three hits and drove in two runs, 
including the go-ahead run in the top of the eighth, as Fullerton (12-11-1, 
6-6) defeated Cypress (20-6, 7-3). Mark Veronda had four hits for the Hornets, 
who rallied from a 5-1 deficit. Mark Selway had a big day for the Chargers with 
a home run, two singles, a double and five RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 3, Saddleback 2 -- Orange Coast (4-16, 1-11) ended a 13-game 
losing streak as George Wise pitched a complete-game seven-hitter over 
Saddleback (12-8-1, 7-5). Kerry Cosgrove got three hits, including two doubles 
and two RBIs. Richard Ernst had two hits, including a triple, and scored a run, 
and Mando Fonseca got two hits and scored a run. Tim Wolter had three hits 
including a double and two RBIs for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Golden West Easter Invitational swim meet: 
</P>
<P>
 Koerner sweeps freestyle sprints -- Chris Koerner won the 50 freestyle 
(21.92), 100 freestyle (48.61), and 200 freestyle (1:47.93) for Golden West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
