<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL ROUNDUP; SOUTHLAND'S IRGUN WINS THE GOTHAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Anita-based Irgun won the $250,000 Gotham Stakes at Aqueduct by six 
lengths Saturday in only his third start. 
</P>
<P>
 Irgun, ridden by Jerry Bailey and carrying 114 pounds, pressed the pace before 
taking command on the turn, and pulled away to cover the mile in 1:36 1/5 over 
the fast main track. 
</P>
<P>
 The colt, trained by Steven Young, scored his second victory and earned 
$150,000 for owners Marianne and Brandon Chase. 
</P>
<P>
 Irgun made his racing debut in February at Santa Anita, breaking his maiden 
impressively at 6 1/2 furlongs, and then finished a strong second in an 
allowance race earlier this month before shipping to New York. Young said that 
he will keep Irgun in New York for the Wood Memorial on April 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Irgun returned $5.40, $4.00 and $3.20. Bit Of Puddin paid $7.80 and $5.40 and 
Jesse F returned $6.60. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gothland, ridden by Corey Nakatani, beat Emerald Jig by a nose to win the 
$200,000 San Francisco Mile at Golden Gate Fields in 1:35 2/5 on the turf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
