<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORKMAN SUSPENDED; 8 KNICKS FINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Haywoode Workman of Indiana and eight New York Knicks were fined by the NBA on 
Saturday, and Workman also received a one-game suspension for Friday night's 
altercation. 
</P>
<P>
 Workman was fined $5,000 and suspended for head-butting Greg Anthony, and 
Anthony was fined $2,500 for retaliating.  
</P>
<P>
 Fined $2,500 for leaving the bench were Charles Smith, Derek Harper, Rolando 
Blackman, Eric Anderson, Anthony Bonner, Corey Gaines and Herb Williams of New 
York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
