<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN TOSSED FROM CLUB ACCUSED OF FIRING AT BOUNCERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old Tustin man -- angered over his ouster from Kokomo's nightclub -- 
returned early Saturday morning and allegedly fired four shots toward the 
security guards who ejected him, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two guards ducked for cover at the sight of the .22 caliber handgun, 
escaping injury.Police said the shooting happened about 1:20 a.m., shortly 
after Nicholas Vacalopoulos was ordered out of the nightclub at 19727 MacArthur 
Blvd. in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that Vacalopoulos had been forced out because he had been drinking 
heavily and creating disturbances. As he left, police said, he made threats to 
the security guards who removed him. 
</P>
<P>
 A few minutes later they saw him again, armed with the handgun. The gunfire 
drew the attention of a police officer who was near the parking lot. According 
to investigators, Vacalopoulos ran away along MacArthur Boulevard, where he 
tossed the gun into some bushes. 
</P>
<P>
 Vacalopoulos was later arrested and charged with assault with intent to commit 
murder. He was being held in the Costa Mesa city jail in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
