<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Ask your nursery professional for the proper spray control for aphids, which 
will soon be opening their 1994 season on your rose growth. 
</P>
<P>
 * If you have a notion to move any azaleas or camellias you have, now is the 
time to do it. 
</P>
<P>
 * To get the most from your spring and summer annuals and perennials, be sure 
to prepare the oil well by adding soil amendments and working the soil to 
eliminate large clumps. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fibrous begonias, cinerarias and impatiens will brighten up the shade 
garden. 
</P>
