<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WILSHIRE / KOREATOWN; PUBLIC INPUT ASKED ON GROWTH 
PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Planning Department will hold another in its series of community 
meetings Thursday to encourage public participation in the revision of the 
General Plan, the document that guides the city's growth and development. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of the Wilshire district, Koreatown, Echo Park and Hollywood are 
invited to attend the meeting, which begins at 6:30 p.m. at A & M Records, 1416 
N. La Brea Ave., in the Charlie Chaplin Sound Stage. 
</P>
<P>
 This phase of community meetings is a preliminary step toward revising the 
plan, last updated in 1974, and will focus on development, transportation and 
economic policy strategies. Information and simultaneous translation (and 
details on child care for the meeting): (800) 376-9675. 
</P>
