<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EL SERENO; LIBRARY PLANS FREE HISTORY, HEALTH TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The El Sereno Branch Public Library plans several free events in April, 
including lectures on health trends and local history. 
</P>
<P>
 A nutritionist from White Memorial Medical Center will speak April 13 on the 
new food pyramid, healthful ways to dine out and how to read and interpret food 
labels.The one-hour discussion begins at 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The El Sereno Coordinating Council will sponsor a historical discussion led by 
environmental planner and historian George Casen about the area from 1769 to 
the 1950s. The April 18 lecture will begin at 5:30 p.m. at El Sereno Recreation 
& Park Auditorium, 4721 Klamath St., and will last about two hours. 
</P>
<P>
 The library, at 4990 Huntington Drive, will hold an astronomy program from 6 
to 8 p.m. April 18, featuring a speaker from Griffith Park Observatory. 
</P>
<P>
 The library also offers free after-school tutoring and a Grandparents and 
Books program, in which senior citizens read to children, from 3 to 4 p.m. 
Mondays and Wednesdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 225-9201. 
</P>
</TEXT>
