COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: SOUTHEAST AREA; CANDIDATE FORUMS SET IN CITY RACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Council candidates in Huntington Park and South Gate will present their 
platforms in two community meetings this week. 
</P>
<P>
 In South Gate, where 11 candidates are competing for three seats, the Chamber 
of Commerce has scheduled a forum at 7 p.m. Wednesday at the South Gate Park 
Auditorium, 4900 Southern Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 567-1203. 
</P>
<P>
 In Huntington Park, where nine candidates are vying for three council seats, 
the Chamber of Commerce will hold a political forum at 6 p.m. Thursday in the 
Huntington Park High School Auditorium, 6020 Miles Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 585-1155. 
</P>
<P>
 During each forum, a moderator will ask candidates to state their views and 
answer questions from the audience. 
