<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: CRENSHAW; SHELTER ACCEPTING 1-PARENT FAMILIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Philanthropy Assn. is accepting applications for its 
single-parent family shelter at 8707 S. Broadway. 
</P>
<P>
 The 99-bed facility, which opened last September, provides shelter for single 
parents and their children. The Crenshaw-based association also serves homeless 
men and women at separate shelters at 1218 S. Norton Ave. and 8311 S. Western 
Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Formed in 1978, the nonprofit association provides shelters, food, clothing, 
books, toys and scholarships for disadvantaged people in South and Central Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 971-4432. 
</P>
</TEXT>
