<P>
 CORONADO -- "The Times of Our Lives" is the theme for the 69th Coronado Flower 
Show, April 9-10 in Spreckels Park on Orange Avenue, between 6th and 7th 
streets. 1-5 p.m. Saturday; 10 a.m.-4 p.m. Sunday. $2, general; $1, kids.Other 
free events in Coronado the same weekend: Art-in-the-Park, "Motorcars and Music 
on Mainstreet," Coronado Friends of the Library Book Fair. (800) 622-8300. SAN 
JUAN CAPISTRANO -- As part of the Fiesta de las Golondrinas, the 17th annual 
Follow the Swallow Run is April 9, beginning at Cook Park/La Novia, Calle 
Arroyo and La Novia Avenue. Starting times: 10K Wheelchair Race, 7:30 a.m.; 10K 
Run, 7:35 a.m.; 4K Fun Run/Stride, 8 a.m.; one-mile fun run for kids, 8:30 a.m. 
Participants encouraged to dress in swallow costumes. (714) 493-5911. 
</P>
<P>
 BORREGO SPRINGS -- The fifth annual Grapefruit Festival, April 13-17, includes 
a classic car show, entertainment and an art show, 9 a.m.-5:30 p.m. Saturday in 
Christmas Circle, and a street dance at 7 p.m. Sunday's festivities, including 
an all-states picnic, are 9:15 a.m.-5 p.m. Also scheduled: Star-gazing at 
Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, 8:30 p.m. Thursday. (800) 824-1884. 
</P>
<P>
 HEALDSBURG -- The scenic, 20th annual Fitch Mountain Footrace (10K run and 3K 
run/walk) starts at 8 a.m. April 17 in Plaza Park. The Healdsburg Spring Crafts 
Faire follows in the park, 10 a.m.-4 p.m. (707) 431-3301. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
