<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; BRITISH TO BEGIN TOLL-FREE SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beginning Monday, the British Tourist Authority office in Los Angeles will no 
longer handle mail inquiries, and its walk-in information bureau will be 
closed. 
</P>
<P>
 A new toll-free telephone number will take the place of both. 
</P>
<P>
 Travelers may call (800) GO2 BRITAIN from 6:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday through 
Friday or write to the BTA, 551 Fifth Ave., Suite 701, New York, N.Y. 10176, 
for information on visiting England, Scotland and Wales. The Authority hopes 
the changes will cut costs and streamline service. 
</P>
