<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; CHARITY: VENICE CENTER GETS $60,000 TO AID THE POOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fritz B. Burns Foundation has awarded $60,000 to St. Joseph's Center in 
Venice. 
</P>
<P>
 A portion of the grant will be used to support the Bread and Roses Cafe, a 
sit-down restaurant that feeds homeless men, women and children. 
</P>
<P>
 The cafe serves about 25,000 meals annually, executive director Rhonda Meister 
said. "This support will ensure that this type of food program continues." 
</P>
<P>
 Funds will also go to the St. Joseph Center Child Care and Parenting Program, 
which provides services to impoverished children and their families. 
</P>
