<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: VENICE; BUS LINE TO CLOSE DUE TO LOW RIDERSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An experimental bus line in Venice will be canceled June 26 due to low 
ridership, the Metropolitan Transportation Authority has announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The cancellation of Line 34 along Rose Avenue will reduce the MTA's operating 
budget deficit by about $268,000 annually, spokesman Steve Chesser said 
Thursday. The line had been instituted in response to customer requests. 
</P>
<P>
 But after one year, the line has averaged only 100 boardings per day, a fourth 
of the anticipated 400. Instead of Line 34, MTA patrons can use Line 33 on Main 
Street, or Santa Monica Municipal Bus Lines' Line 3, boarding on Lincoln 
Boulevard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
